# Distilled from todoclaw's .env.example pattern (ADR-0003 env taxonomy), in
# production 2026-06-23 → 2026-07-03.
# The committed contract of what env the app needs — PLACEHOLDER VALUES ONLY.
# Real values live in .env.local (gitignored). Claude cannot create .env.local —
# the PreToolUse hook blocks .env* writes and key-shaped values by design; creating
# it is a human step. Taxonomy + the three isolated secret stores: docs/SECURITY.md.
#
# At bootstrap, replace these examples with your project's real PUBLIC client vars
# (public-by-design values like an RLS-gated anon key; the access guard is the
# backend policy, not secrecy):
EXAMPLE_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
EXAMPLE_PUBLIC_ANON_KEY=your-local-anon-key-here
#
# Server-only secrets (admin keys, AI keys, DB passwords) NEVER appear in this file,
# never get a client-visible prefix (VITE_/NEXT_PUBLIC_/...), and are set in the host
# env store (e.g. `supabase secrets set`, Vercel env) — not here.
